    "biography": "<p>The bronze golem is a massive, 16-foot-tall humanoid construct made of solid bronze. It resembles a towering fire giant with glowing, molten veins beneath its metal exterior.</p><p><strong>Burning Blood:</strong> Any creature that damages the bronze golem with an edged weapon must make a saving throw vs. death ray or take 2d6 damage as fiery blood spurts from the wound.</p><p><strong>Fiery Strikes:</strong> The bronze golem's melee attacks are superheated, dealing an additional 1d10 fire damage per hit.</p><p><strong>Fire Immunity:</strong> The bronze golem is completely immune to all fire-based attacks, including magical fire.</p><p><strong>Resistances:</strong></p><ul><li>Immune to sleep, charm, and hold spells.</li><li>Does not breathe, making it immune to all gas-based attacks.</li></ul><p><strong>Terrain:</strong> Variable.</p>",
